{{Infobox software | name = Soprano | logo = <!-- [[File: ]] --> | screenshot = <!-- [[File: ]] --> | caption = | collapsible = | author = | developer = Daniele Galdi and Sebastian Trueg (sponsored by [[Mandriva]]) | released = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | latest release version = 2.8.0<ref>{{cite web |url=http://soprano.sourceforge.net/node/63 |title=Soprano 2.8.0 released |author=trueg |date=June 27, 2012 |accessdate=June 30, 2012}}</ref> | latest release date = {{start date and age|2012|06|27}}<!-- {{start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | latest preview version = | latest preview date = <!-- {{start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | frequently updated = yes | programming language = [[C++]] / [[Qt (framework)|Qt]] | operating system = [[Cross-platform]] | platform = | size = 1.9 MB | language = | status = Active | genre = RDF framework | license = [[GNU Lesser General Public License]]<ref>[http://sourceforge.net/projects/soprano/ Soprano in sourceforge]</ref> | website = http://soprano.sourceforge.net/ }} {{Portal|Free software}} '''Soprano''' is a software library that provides an object-oriented C++/Qt4 framework for [[Resource Description Framework|RDF]] data. Soprano was created as a sub project under the [[NEPOMUK (framework)|NEPOMUK]] project and forms a part of the semantic desktop in [[KDE Software Compilation 4]]. Soprano functions as a repository to store information generated by the NEPOMUK server (like ratings, tags or comments), which will then be indexed by [[Strigi]] for better search results.<ref>[http://liquidat.wordpress.com/2007/06/19/more-about-nepomuk-kde-soprano-and-kde-integration/ More about Nepomuk-KDE: Soprano and KDE integration]</ref>
Soprano comes with support for [[Redland RDF Application Framework|redland]] and [[Sesame (framework)|Sesame2]] backends for actually storing and querying the RDF data.<ref>[http://soprano.sourceforge.net/node/19 Soprano homepage ]</ref>
== Features == * Simple plugin design, with 5 different classes of plugins * Server/client architecture which allows to run an RDF storage remotely. Interfaces for communication over TCP, Unix sockets, and D-Bus are provided * Fully documented API using [[Doxygen]] * [[Lucene|CLucene]] index which provides a full-text query index
